@Merkle | SN87 | CheckerChain , So what's your solution on duplication?
If two miners are so good that they predict duplicate scores, both of them will eventually get deregistered because they get low emissions.
However, a bad miner, who is not so good as the above two, will survive because it still gets emissions.

@Sandip | SN87 | CheckerChain, The closer my miner's prediction score is to the actual score, the higher possibility of duplication it has.
In a result, it'll be more likely to get low emissions unless it's lucky to be always selected in case of duplication.
I'm afraid this is not good.

